caption.text: Picture this: Image generation in the Gemini app is now even better with Imagen 4. 🖼 Create richer images with more nuance and details — even text and typography
More fun with Veo 3. ✨ Now available in 70+ countries AND Google AI Pro subscribers can try it too
Need an ingredient check? Gemini Live can chat about what you see. Just tap the new camera icon ✨
We love seeing how you’re using AI Mode 🔎. Rolling out now in the U.S. Try in Labs today.
Say hi to Google’s most helpful AI. 👋✨#GoogleIO

Last year, we introduced Project Astra – a research prototype exploring capabilities for a universal AI assistant. 🤝

We’ve been making it even better with improved voice output, memory and computer control - so it can be more personalized and proactive.
ICYMI: Here are 11 highlights from #GoogleIO. ➡ for some of our top announcements, then tap the link in our bio to learn more.
It’s officially Gemini season. ♊ Start vibe coding with Canvas and 2.5 Pro in the Gemini app
Surreal scenes from a day on Earth, created with Imagen 4 in the Gemini app ✨
See what clothes look like on you before you buy. 👖 Test out our new try on tool in Search Labs in the U.S.
Go with the Flow 🌊 Create clips and scenes with the combined power of Veo, Imagen and Gemini.
Summer’s calling! ☀ Turn your pics into games with Gemini 2.5 Pro
Here’s a first look at Android XR on glasses, with Gemini built-in 👀
Need help visualizing a complex topic? Get stats, graphs and charts in AI Mode — starting with sports and finance this summer 📈
What a lineup! 🤩 Imagen 4 in the Gemini app is now even better at text. Which poster is your fave?
Introducing near real-time speech translation in Google Meet. People can now have natural, free-flowing conversations — while speaking different languages. 🗣
Everything new for Gemini we announced at #GoogleIO, from Imagen 4 and Veo 3 to Gemini Live and Deep Research updates ✨
Google Beam, our new AI-first video communication platform, transforms standard video streams into immersive 3D experiences.
Project Astra’s Visual Interpreter is helping people who are blind and low-vision navigate the world
Get help finding event tickets, restaurant reservations and local appointments without hassle: Just let AI Mode in Search do the heavy lifting. Coming soon to Labs.
This summer, AI Mode in Labs will be able to give you personalized suggestions based on your past searches. See how it works.
Feeling lucky? Try vibe coding with Canvas and 2.5 Pro in the Gemini app ✨
Get a look at glasses with Android XR, built for the Gemini era. 👓
Bring a range of styles to life in Imagen 4. Now available in the Gemini app ⚡
AI Mode is our most powerful AI search. Ask anything, and it’ll take on your toughest questions and help you get stuff done. Now rolling out to everyone in the U.S.
7 webcam experiments using Gemini 2.5 Pro in @googlegemini and AI Studio ✨. What've you been making?
Stitched with Imagen 4. 🌴 Try it now in the Gemini app
Project Astra’s Live capabilities, coming soon to AI Mode in Search. 🔍
Super G, meet Veo 2. ✨ Go from text to video in the @googlegemini app.
Gemini keeps it real. 😎 Share your camera in Gemini Live to ask questions about what you see.
Watch Gemini 2.5 Pro simulate an entirely new universe in the @googlegemini app. 🌌

Since last year’s #GoogleIO, we've introduced over a dozen models and research breakthroughs and released over 20 major AI products and features. Today @sundarpichai reflected on this relentless progress — and the AI opportunities in our future. Tap the link in our bio to learn more.

Starting today, our latest and most capable image generation model is available in Gemini: Meet Imagen 4.

The images are richer, with more nuanced colors and fine-grain details. #GoogleIO

Imagen 4 is available for users to try today in the app.

Video, meet audio. 🎥🤝🔊

With Veo 3, our new state-of-the-art generative video model, you can directly add soundtracks to clips you make.

🗣 Create talking characters
🔔 Add sound effects
🚦 Include ambient background audio 

Scroll to see more - sound on. ➡
Ask AI Mode anything. Rolling out to everyone in the U.S. starting today 🚀
Don’t forget to tune into #GoogleIO, streaming live tomorrow, May 20 at 10 am PT. Learn more at io.google.
